a filter more than once, in which case it will be run more"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"than once.  Filters added during a filter callback won’t be run on","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the message being processed. Filter functions are allowed to modify"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and even drop messages."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"addFilter","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"filterFunction","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GDBusMessageFilterFunction","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GDBusMessageFilterFunction"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userData"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer"},{"text":"? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"userDataFreeFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GDestroyNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@GDestroyNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?) -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that filters are run in a dedicated message handling thread so"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"they can’t block and, generally, can’t do anything but signal a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"worker thread. Also note that filters are rarely needed - use API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"such as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_send_message_with_reply()"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_subscribe()"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_call()"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If a filter consumes an incoming message the message is not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"dispatched anywhere else - not even the standard dispatch machinery","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(that API such as "},{"code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_subscribe()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_send_message_with_reply()"},{"type":"text","text":" relies on) will see the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"message. Similarly, if a filter consumes an outgoing message, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"message will not be sent to the other peer."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"userDataFreeFunc"},{"type":"text","text":" is non-"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", it will be called (in the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"thread-default main context of the thread you are calling this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"method from) at some point after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"userData"},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"needed. (It is not guaranteed to be called synchronously when the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"filter is removed, and may be called after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"connection"},{"type":"text","text":" has been"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"destroyed.)","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/dbusconnection\/addfilter(filterfunction:userdata:userdatafreefunc:)"],"traits":[